en.purpose: To record additional composition metadata aligned with IHE-XDS which is not already available from the Reference Model COMPOSITION class.
en.use: Use to add IHE-XDS aligned metadata to a COMPOSITION.context, which along with existing COMPOSITION attributes, allows the composition to be registered in an IHE-XDS environment.

at0000.description: Additional composition metadata aligned with IHE-XDS which is not already available from the Reference Model COMPOSITION class.

at0001.description: The speciality of the author/composer of the document.

at0002.description: A high-level document class code, normally selected from a valueset provided by the IHE-XDS Affinity Domain.
at0002.comment:
For example: Report, Summary, Images, Plan, Patient Preferences, Workflow.
These codes are specific to an XDS Affinity Domain.

at0003.description: The code specifying the precise type of document from the user perspective. Normally selected from a valueset provided by the local IHE-XDS Affinity Domain or national standard.
at0003.comment:
for example:  Pulmonary History and Physical, Discharge Summary, Ultrasound Report.
These codes are specific to an XDS Affinity Domain.

at0004.description: A term specifying the level of confidentiality of the XDS Document.
at0004.comment: Coded text is preferred, normally specific to an XDS Affinity Domain.

at0009.description: The code specifying the clinical specialty where the act that resulted in the document was performed.
at0009.comment:
For example: Family Practice, Laboratory, Radiology.
Coded text is preferred, normally specific to an XDS Affinity Domain.

at0010.description: Additional metadata about the document itself, including size, url.

at0011.description: This list of codes represents the main clinical acts.

en.purpose: To record the results and total score of the GAD-7 scale.
en.use: Use to record the results and total score of the GAD-7 scale.

at0000.description: Generalized Anxiety Disorder 7-item (GAD-7) scale recording the experience of anxiety related symptoms in the previous two weeks.

at0002.description: Default, unspecified point in time or interval event which may be explicitly defined in a template or at run-time.

at0005.description: Additional information required to capture local context or to align with other reference models/formalisms.
at0005.comment: e.g. Local hospital departmental infomation or additional metadata to align with HL7 or CDISC equivalents.

at0007.description: Record any issues or factors that may impact on the score or it's interpretation.

at0008.text: Feeling nervous, anxious or on edge
at0008.description: Over the last 2 weeks, on how many days have you felt nervous, anxious or on edge?

at0009.description: The patient reports that they have not felt nervous, anxious or on edge at all over the last 2 weeks.

at0010.description: The patient reports that they have felt nervous, anxious or on edge several days over the last 2 weeks.

at0011.description: The patient reports that they have felt nervous, anxious or on edge more than half the days over the last 2 weeks.

at0012.description: The patient reports that they have felt nervous, anxious or on edge over the last 2 weeks.

at0013.text: Not being able to stop or control worrying
at0013.description: Over the last 2 weeks, on how many days have you not been able to stop or control worrying?

at0014.description: The patient reports that they have not at all been affected by not being able to stop or control worrying over the last 2 weeks.

at0015.description: The patient reports that they have not been able to stop or control worrying several days over the last 2 weeks.

at0016.description: The patient reports that they have not been able to stop or control worrying more than half the days over the last 2 weeks.

at0017.description: The patient reports that they have not been able to stop or control worrying nearly every day over the last 2 weeks.

at0018.text: Worrying too much about different things
at0018.description: Over the last 2 weeks, on how many days have you been worrying too much about different things?

at0019.description: The patient reports that they have not at all been affected by worrying too much about different things over the last 2 weeks.

at0020.description: The patient reports that they have been worrying too much about different things several days over the last 2 weeks.

at0021.description: The patient reports that they have been worrying too much about different things more than half the days over the last 2 weeks.

at0022.description: The patient reports that they have been worrying too much about different things nearly every day over the last 2 weeks.

at0023.description: Over the last 2 weeks, on how many days have you had trouble relaxing?

at0024.description: The patient reports that they have not at all had trouble relaxing over the last 2 weeks.

at0025.description: The patient reports that they have had trouble relaxing several days over the last 2 weeks.

at0026.description: The patient reports that they have had trouble relaxing more than half the days over the last 2 weeks.

at0027.description: The patient reports that they have had trouble relaxing nearly every day over the last 2 weeks.

at0028.text: Being so restless it is hard to sit still
at0028.description: Over the last 2 weeks, on how many days have you been so restless it is hard to sit still?

at0029.description: The patient reports that they have not at all been affected by being so restless it is hard to sit still over the last 2 weeks.

at0030.description: The patient reports that they had been so restless it is hard to sit still several days over the last 2 weeks.

at0031.description: The patient reports that they had been so restless it is hard to sit still more than half the days over the last 2 weeks.

at0032.description: The patient reports that they had been so restless it is hard to sit still nearly every day over the last 2 weeks.

at0033.description: Over the last 2 weeks, on how many days have you become easily annoyed or irritable?

at0034.description: The patient reports that they have not at all been affected by becoming easily annoyed or irritable over the last 2 weeks.

at0035.description: The patient reports that they have become easily annoyed or irritable several days over the last 2 weeks.

at0036.description: The patient reports that they have become easily annoyed or irritable more than half the days over the last 2 weeks.

at0037.description: The patient reports that they have become easily annoyed or irritable nearly every day over the last 2 weeks.

at0038.text: Feeling afraid as it something awful might happen
at0038.description: Over the last 2 weeks, on how many days have you felt afraid as if something awful might happen?

at0039.description: The patient reports that they have not at all been affected by feeling afraid as if something awful might happen over the last 2 weeks.

at0040.description: The patient reports that they have felt afraid as if something awful might happen several days over the last 2 weeks.

at0041.description: The patient reports that they have felt afraid as if something awful might happen more than half the days over the last 2 weeks.

at0042.description: The patient reports that they have felt afraid as if something awful might happen nearly every day over the last 2 weeks.

at0043.description: Total GAD-7 score calculated from sum of all seven individual responses.
